      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "body": "5 cloves optional.",
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Put the sugar, water, lemon juice, and cinnamon stick in a medium pot over a medium heat. Simmer, stirring now and then, until the sugar dissolves.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Peel and core the pears and cut into quarters, and add them to the pot.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Simmer for 10-15 minutes or until the fruit is soft and begins to break down. Remove and discard the cinnamon stick and cloves.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Serve hot with ice cream.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Note - Can be eaten hot or cold. This is delicious on yoghurt, pancakes, waffles, ice cream, granola or cheesecake. Get creative with the tasty stewed pears.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Churn to a soft-serve consistency before freezing. Pre-chill the bowl overnight if using a bowl-style ice cream maker.",
              "cause": "Mixture had too much water, or didn't churn long enough.",
              "symptom": "Ice crystals form on freezing"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Take out 15 minutes before serving to soften. Next time, scale up sugar by 10 to 20 grams per 500 ml of mixture.",
              "cause": "Sugar level too low, sugar prevents freezing solid.",
              "symptom": "Texture is too hard from the freezer"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Temper, pour a ladle of hot milk into the yolks first, whisking, then return to the pan over low heat. Don't let it boil.",
              "cause": "Heat too high, or eggs went in cold and fast.",
              "symptom": "Custard split when warming"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Whip cream to soft peaks (it flops slightly when the whisk is lifted). Fold in with a metal spoon, cutting through the centre and lifting from the base.",
              "cause": "Cream wasn't whipped enough, or it was folded in too vigorously.",
              "symptom": "Mousse won't hold its shape"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Boozy version: stir in 2 tablespoons of dark rum, brandy, or liqueur once the mix is churned, the alcohol stops it freezing hard.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Chocolate ripple: drizzle warm chocolate sauce through the churned mix before freezing, and don't over-stir.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Made days in advance and lives in the freezer.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
